div.div:
FIX: Refactor accounting calculations to align with current month/year
Removed the usage of 'lastMonth' value in calculation of sums in 'AccountingMain.php'. Now, it aligns calculations with the current year and current month, thereby improving the accuracy in measuring metrics in the accounting system irrespective of the time period.

FIX: Remove lastMonth value from accounting calculation
The 'lastMonth' value has been removed from the expenses calculation in 'AccountingMain.php' for more accurate results. This change improves the computation of metrics in the accounting system by aligning the outstanding amount with the total expenses, regardless of the time period.

PATCH: Refactor metrics calculation in AccountingMain
Metrics calculation has been restructured in 'AccountingMain.php' to enhance precision. The changes involve reformatting the return of 'outstanding_amount', 'overdue_amount', and 'expenses' to provide more specific details. These modifications improve the handling of different order payments status and ensure accurate calculation.

Refactor metrics and accounting information
Accounting and metrics display have been refactored for more precision. The changes improve the return types in diff and calculate metric methods in the AccountingMain class. This refactoring allows for better handling of various order payment statuses and ensures greater accuracy in reporting.

PATCH: Refactor ShopStatistics and AccountingMain for flexibility
Updated several methods in ShopStatistics and AccountingMain classes to provide more detailed calculations and allow for greater flexibility in handling different statuses of order payments. Also, return types were improved in diff and calculate metric methods for greater precision and type safety.
